From: experintellia <280144245+experintellia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 22:57:40 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 26/42] web-app: explain webimap setup failures in the failure
 alert, not up front

Replaces the pre-flight reachability/CORS probe in the madmail-server
dialog. The probe tried to disambiguate a failed cross-origin fetch
(dead host vs. missing CORS headers) before onboarding, but every
heuristic variant misdiagnosed working servers: probing / hit a page
madmail serves without CORS headers, probing /webimap/mailboxes still
read slow or webimap-only-CORS servers as unreachable. A warning that
cries wolf on working servers is worse than none.

Instead, when webimap account creation actually fails, append the
troubleshooting info to the real error alert in the instant-onboarding
flow: check the address / server is online, webimap+websmtp enabled,
and CORS (Access-Control-Allow-Origin) configured, pointing at the
madmail webimap docs. AlertDialog renders with white-space:
break-spaces, so the multi-line checklist displays as written. No
network guessing, no false warnings, and the hints appear exactly when
the opaque NetworkError does.

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 .../src/hooks/useInstantOnboarding.ts         | 29 +++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 29 insertions(+)

diff --git a/packages/frontend/src/hooks/useInstantOnboarding.ts b/packages/frontend/src/hooks/useInstantOnboarding.ts
index 15785bbc7..1aabccd89 100644
--- a/packages/frontend/src/hooks/useInstantOnboarding.ts
+++ b/packages/frontend/src/hooks/useInstantOnboarding.ts
@@ -138,6 +138,35 @@ export default function useInstantOnboarding(): InstantOnboarding {
             }
           },
           onFail: error => {
+            // webimap account creation runs over the browser's own fetch
+            // (POST <server>/new, then the login check). A failed cross-origin
+            // fetch surfaces as an opaque "NetworkError" — which the core then
+            // wraps with a long wasm stack backtrace that tells the user
+            // nothing. Drop the backtrace (everything from the "Stack
+            // backtrace:" marker on, so a multi-line message or `Caused by:`
+            // chain still survives) and lead with an actionable checklist of
+            // what's actually worth checking. (An earlier up-front
+            // reachability/CORS probe was removed: every heuristic variant
+            // misdiagnosed working servers, e.g. slow servers read as
+            // unreachable.)
+            if (/^webimapaccount:/i.test(configurationQR)) {
+              const host = configurationQR.replace(/^webimapaccount:/i, '')
+              const summary = String(error)
+                .split(/\n\s*stack backtrace:/i)[0]
+                .trim()
+              openDialog(AlertDialog, {
+                message:
+                  `Could not set up an account on the madmail server ` +
+                  `"${host}". Please check that:\n` +
+                  `— the address is correct and the server is online\n` +
+                  `— the server has webimap and websmtp enabled\n` +
+                  `— the server permits browser apps (CORS): it must answer ` +
+                  `with Access-Control-Allow-Origin headers, see the madmail ` +
+                  `webimap docs (TDD 10-webimap)` +
+                  (summary ? `\n\n${summary}` : ''),
+              })
+              return
+            }
             openDialog(AlertDialog, { message: error })
           },
         })
